Certainly! Here's an example of a table in HTML with an edit button that allows you to change cell content:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Table Example with Editable Cell Content</title>
  <style>
    table {
      border-collapse: collapse;
      width: 100%;
    }
    th, td {
      border: 1px solid black;
      padding: 8px;
      text-align: left;
    }
    th {
      background-color: #ccc;
    }
    tr:nth-child(even) {
      background-color: #f2f2f2;
    }
    .edit-button {
      padding: 4px 8px;
      background-color: #4CAF50;
      color: white;
      border: none;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    .edit-button:hover {
      background-color: #45a049;
    }
  </style>
  <script>
    function makeEditable(cell) {
      cell.contentEditable = true;
      cell.focus();
    }
  </script>
</head>
<body>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Column 1</th>
        <th>Column 2</th>
        <th>Column 3</th>
        <th>Edit</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td onclick="makeEditable(this)">Cell 1</td>
        <td onclick="makeEditable(this)">Cell 2</td>
        <td onclick="makeEditable(this)">Cell 3</td>
        <td><button class="edit-button">Edit</button></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td onclick="makeEditable(this)">Cell 4</td>
        <td onclick="makeEditable(this)">Cell 5</td>
        <td onclick="makeEditable(this)">Cell 6</td>
        <td><button class="edit-button">Edit</button></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td onclick="makeEditable(this)">Cell 7</td>
        <td onclick="makeEditable(this)">Cell 8</td>
        <td onclick="makeEditable(this)">Cell 9</td>
        <td><button class="edit-button">Edit</button></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</body>
</html>
```

In this example, a JavaScript function `makeEditable()` is added to enable editing when a table cell is clicked. When a cell is clicked, it becomes editable using the `contentEditable` property set to true for that cell. Additionally, an "Edit" button is provided for each row. However, please note that saving the changes made to the cell content is not covered in this example as it requires additional handling, such as storing the modified data in a database or using JavaScript to update the backend.

